questions.text:
Analyze the oxoacids of Sulfur provided in Column I and match them with their characteristic structural features or oxidation states listed in Column II. Select the option that represents the correct sequential pairing.

 egin{itemize}
    \item [A] Peroxodisulfuric acid ($H_2S_2O_8$)
    \item [B] Dithionic acid ($H_2S_2O_6$)
    \item [C] Pyrosulfuric acid ($H_2S_2O_7$)
    \item [D] Sulfurous acid ($H_2SO_3$)
\end{itemize}

 egin{itemize}
    \item [(p)] Contains $S-S$ bond; Sulfur in $+5$ state
    \item [(q)] Contains $S-O-O-S$ linkage; Sulfur in $+6$ state
    \item [(r)] Contains $S-O-S$ linkage; Sulfur in $+6$ state
    \item [(s)] Contains a lone pair on Sulfur; Sulfur in $+4$ state
\end{itemize}
